 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Quality Score in High-throughput Sequencing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "In this notebook, I have arranged the information on websites and created the notes about quality score used in High-throughput sequencing."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "### import libraries\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "plt.style.use('seaborn-whitegrid')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "### set directories/constants\n",
    "DIR_DAT_RAW  = \"/home/jovyan/work/Data/SRR4841864/rawdata\"\n",
    "DIR_DAT_TRIM = \"/home/jovyan/work/Data/SRR4841864/trimmed_fastqs/\"\n",
    "DIR_CUR      = \"/home/jovyan/work/GitRepo/Duke_CBB520_HW2\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## How is the quality score store in fastq"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The quality score is stored in the fourth line of each read"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "\n",
      "====================================================\n",
      "Line  0 : @SRR4841864.1 1 length=101\n",
      "Line  1 : NGGCATACCAATGGGAAGAGCATGCGTGGGAATGGTATTCAAAAATCGAGAAAGAAGGATGCTGCTGCTGCTGCCGCTGTTGGGAAAGCTATAAAGGATGA\n",
      "Line  2 : +SRR4841864.1 1 length=101\n",
      "Line  3 : #1:BDFFFDHFHDGGBBGGHGIGGHEHGIFIHGFDB?FHGHIIIDDGFHGCHIIIIIIIIIHGCCCBBDFDFCCECCCCBCCCBBABBCCCCCCECCCCCC\n",
      "\n",
      "====================================================\n",
      "Line  4 : @SRR4841864.2 2 length=101\n",
      "Line  5 : NAGCTTCGTTAAGACTTTGACTGGTAAGACCATCACTTTGGAAGTTGAATCTTCTGACACCATTGACAATGTCAAGTCCAAGATCCAAGACAAGGAAGGTA\n",
      "Line  6 : +SRR4841864.2 2 length=101\n",
      "Line  7 : #1=BDDDD?CFFFIIEFIFFHFIEFHIBHFFEFEFFIFEFIIFE<<?D?DGFIFIIGFEDFFIEGFFGGCC7@EFE7=AEEEDDDDDC@CCCBBBBBBBA>\n",
      "\n",
      "====================================================\n",
      "Line  8 : @SRR4841864.3 3 length=101\n",
      "Line  9 : NTTATATCTATGAATGAATATGCATTGCTCTTCTGATACTATGGTATGAGAGGCCTTGGTAAAGGGCATCGATAACCGAAAGAATCATCCGCAGAGAAGTA\n",
      "Line 10 : +SRR4841864.3 3 length=101\n",
      "Line 11 : #1=?DDD?F?D8<FEGBABHBA<FHE93AAAHD<AFEG4?:ED<?DD<B4B918B@?FH8BDG?)BDFDHID@6;3=:59=<ACCCA@>CBB8?B253<:3\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "with open(os.path.join(DIR_DAT_RAW, \"SRR4841864_1.fastq\"), 'r') as fp:\n",
    "    for cnt, line in enumerate(fp):\n",
    "        line = line.strip()\n",
    "        if cnt % 4 == 0:\n",
    "            print(\"\\n====================================================\")\n",
    "        print(\"Line {0:^3}: {1}\".format(cnt, line))\n",
    "        if cnt > 10:\n",
    "            break"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction to Quality Score in Sequencing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The ASCII number of each character is called the phred score, which can be converted to the probability of error."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The relationship of phred score Q and error probability P for each base is:\n",
    "$$Q = -10 \\log_{10} P$$\n",
    "$$P = 10^{-\\frac{Q}{10}}$$"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "There are two ways of setting the phred score and the Ascii code: phred+33 or phred+44  "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Phred  Prob of   Phred+33  Phred+64\n",
      "score   Error     Ascii     Ascii  \n",

      "  2    0.63096     #         B    \n",

      "  4    0.39811     %         D    \n",
      "  5    0.31623     &         E    \n",

      " 20    0.01000     5         T    \n",
      " 21    0.00794     6         U    \n",
      " 22    0.00631     7         V    \n",
      " 23    0.00501     8         W    \n",
      " 24    0.00398     9         X    \n",
      " 25    0.00316     :         Y    \n",
      " 26    0.00251     ;         Z    \n",
      " 27    0.00200     <         [    \n",
      " 28    0.00158     =         \\    \n",
      " 29    0.00126     >         ]    \n",
      " 30    0.00100     ?         ^    \n",
      " 31    0.00079     @         _    \n",
      " 32    0.00063     A         `    \n",
      " 33    0.00050     B         a    \n",
      " 34    0.00040     C         b    \n",
      " 35    0.00032     D         c    \n",
      " 36    0.00025     E         d    \n",
      " 37    0.00020     F         e    \n",
      " 38    0.00016     G         f    \n",
      " 39    0.00013     H         g    \n",
      " 40    0.00010     I         h    \n",
      " 41    0.00008     J         i    \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def error_prob(quality):\n",
    "    qval = quality\n",
    "    return 10**(qval/-10.0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print (\"{0:^5}  {1:^8}  {2:^8}  {3:^8}\".format(\"Phred\",  \"Prob of\", \"Phred+33\", \"Phred+64\"))\n",
    "print (\"{0:^5}  {1:^8}  {2:^8}  {3:^8}\".format(\"score\",  \"Error\", \"Ascii\", \"Ascii\"))\n",
    "for phred in range(0,42):\n",
    "    print (\"{0:^5}  {1:03.5f}  {2:^8}  {3:^8}\".format(phred, error_prob(phred), chr(phred+33), chr(phred+64)))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Visualization of Phred Score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 936x360 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(ncols=2, nrows=1, figsize=(13,5))\n",
    "\n",
    "### read 1\n",
    "ax = axes[0]\n",
    "with open(os.path.join(DIR_DAT_RAW, \"SRR4841864_1.fastq\"), 'r') as fp:\n",
    "    for cnt, line in enumerate(fp):\n",
    "        if cnt > 100:\n",
    "            break   \n",
    "        if cnt % 4 == 3:\n",
    "            line = line.strip()\n",
    "            phred = [ord(char)-33      for char  in line ]\n",
    "            prob  = [error_prob(score) for score in phred]\n",
    "            ax.plot(phred)\n",
    "\n",
    "### read 2\n",
    "ax = axes[1]\n",
    "with open(os.path.join(DIR_DAT_RAW, \"SRR4841864_2.fastq\"), 'r') as fp:\n",
    "    for cnt, line in enumerate(fp):\n",
    "        if cnt > 64:\n",
    "            break   \n",
    "        if cnt % 4 == 3:\n",
    "            line = line.strip()\n",
    "            phred = [ord(char)-33      for char  in line ]\n",
    "            prob  = [error_prob(score) for score in phred]\n",
    "            ax.plot(phred)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Set plot axes\n",
    "ax1, ax2 = axes\n",
    "ax1.set_title(\"SRR4841864_1.fastq\")\n",
    "ax2.set_title(\"SRR4841864_2.fastq\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_ylim([0, 42])\n",
    "ax2.set_ylim([0, 42])\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_xlabel(\"Index of Bases\")\n",
    "ax2.set_xlabel(\"Index of Bases\")\n",
    "\n",
    "ax1.set_ylabel(\"Phred Score\")\n",
    "ax2.set_ylabel(\"Phred Score\")\n",
    "pass"
   ]
  },
